          <td><strong>Post-fire flooding and debris flow</strong></td>
          <td>High in burn scar areas</td>
          <td>Post-fire debris flows are a serious secondary hazard in New Mexico's mountain terrain. After the 2022 fire, burn scar flooding affected communities in San Miguel and Mora counties during monsoon season 2022 and 2023. Standard homeowners policies do not cover flood.</td>
        </tr>
